<LABEL>The sixteenth tels them the vanitie of such practises.</LABEL>
<ITEM><HI>225</HI></ITEM>
<LABEL>The seuenteenth forbids them a respectiue Religion.</LABEL>
<ITEM><HI>226</HI></ITEM>
<LABEL>The eighteenth discourageth from countenancing such.</LABEL>
<ITEM><HI>227</HI></ITEM>
<LABEL>The nineteenth tends to the inlighting of Magistrates.</LABEL>
<ITEM><HI>228</HI></ITEM>
<LABEL>The twentith giues them their due commendation.</LABEL>
<ITEM><HI>229</HI></ITEM>
<LABEL>The twentith one checketh the careles ministers.</LABEL>
<ITEM><HI>230</HI></ITEM>
<LABEL>The twentith two stirres them vp.</LABEL>
<ITEM><HI>231</HI></ITEM>
<LABEL>The twentith three commends priuate mislikers.</LABEL>
<ITEM><HI>232</HI></ITEM>
<LABEL>The twentith foure stirres them to thankefulnes.</LABEL>
<ITEM><HI>234</HI></ITEM>
<LABEL>How we are to esteeme of the extraordinarie passions of people in these our daies.</LABEL>
<ITEM><HI>236</HI></ITEM>
<LABEL>The summarie of all this encounter is drawne into foure seuerall questions.</LABEL>
<ITEM></ITEM>
</LIST>
</DIV2>
<TRAILER><GAP DESC="foreign"> So be it.</TRAILER>
